 :tx/rationale "Create task: CE-TOPO: Topological hole detection — Betti numbers for the knowledge complex. CONTEXT: FEGH only detects H0 holes (disconnected components). H1 (circular reasoning) and H2 (bounded unknowns) are invisible. Three different Socratic strategies needed for three hole types. RATIONALE: The topology of ignorance determines the optimal questioning strategy. H0 needs bridges, H1 needs falsification, H2 needs exploration. INV-CONVERGENCE-007. APPROACH: (1) Add compute_knowledge_topology(store) -> KnowledgeTopology to a new module crates/braid-kernel/src/knowledge_topology.rs. KnowledgeTopology: { beta0: usize, beta1: usize, components: Vec<Vec<EntityId>>, cycles: Vec<Vec<EntityId>> }. (2) beta0 computation: count connected components in the observation connection graph. Reuse existing connected_components() from query/graph.rs or implement via BFS/DFS on :connection/* edges. (3) beta1 computation: detect cycles in the connection graph. A cycle exists when there is a path from observation A back to A through connections. Use DFS with back-edge detection. Each back-edge indicates one H1 cycle. (4) beta2 (simplified): count observation entities that have 3+ connections ALL pointing to the same community but the entity itself is NOT connected to entities outside that community. These are boundary observations of unexplored voids. Full H2 requires simplicial homology which is expensive — use this proxy. (5) Surface in braid status: 'topology: N components, M loops, K voids' when observation count >= 10 and connection count >= 5. Below threshold, omit (not enough data for meaningful topology). (6) Wire into FEGH hypothesis type selection: H0 -> bridge hypothesis, H1 -> falsification hypothesis (new), H2 -> void-exploration hypothesis (new). (7) Euler characteristic chi = beta0 - beta1 + beta2 as a single convergence metric alongside F(S). ACCEPTANCE: (A) 3 disconnected observation clusters: beta0=3. (B) Circular path A->B->C->A detected: beta1>=1. (C) Boundary observations of unexplored area: beta2 proxy > 0. (D) braid status shows topology line when threshold met. (E) FEGH generates falsification hypothesis for H1 cycle. (F) FEGH generates void-exploration hypothesis for H2 void. (G) Euler characteristic computed and surfaceable. DEPENDS-ON: CE-CONN (provides the connection graph). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/knowledge_topology.rs (new) + crates/braid-kernel/src/routing.rs (hypothesis type selection)"
